.TH ALEA 1 "2026-05-13" "alea 0.9.12" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
alea \- verifiable random selection using drand
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B alea
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.I option1 option2
.RI [ option3 .\|.\|.]
.br
.B alea
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.B \-\-file
.I path
.RB [ \-\-delimiter
.IR delim ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B alea
makes random selections using the drand distributed randomness beacon.
Every result is tied to a specific drand round and can be independently
verified by anyone.
.PP
Given two or more options,
.B alea
fetches a randomness value from the drand network, computes an index from
the first 8 hex characters (32 bits), and selects the winner as
.IR index " % " option_count .
.PP
For multiple winners, each pick uses the next 8 hex characters and removes
the chosen option from the pool before the next draw.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-round " N"
Use a specific drand round for verification. Mutually exclusive with
.BR \-\-at .
.TP
.BI \-\-at " TIMESTAMP"
Calculate the drand round for a specific time (ISO 8601 format).
If the time is in the future, prints a scheduled run command.
If in the past, prints a historical run command.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-file " " \fIpath\fR
Read options from a file, one per line. Use
.B \-
to read from stdin.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-delimiter " " \fIstr\fR
Split file input by
.I str
instead of newline.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-count " " \fIN\fR
Pick
.I N
unique winners in ranked order. Maximum 8.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Print only the winner(s), no headers or metadata. Useful for scripting.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output results as JSON.
.TP
.B \-\-tsv
Output results as tab-separated key/value pairs.
.TP
.B \-\-sh
Show a bash/zsh verification oneliner. Single winner only.
.TP
.B \-\-fish
Show a fish shell verification oneliner. Single winner only.
.TP
.B \-\-ps
Show a PowerShell verification oneliner. Single winner only.
.TP
.B \-\-all
Show all verification methods (alea, bash, fish, PowerShell).
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print usage summary and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Runtime error (network failure, drand unavailable).
.TP
.B 2
Usage error (invalid arguments, missing options).
.SH EXAMPLES
Pick a random lunch option:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ alea pizza sushi tacos ramen
.fi
.RE
.PP
Verify a past result (same round + same options = same result):
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ alea \-\-round 6100001 pizza sushi tacos ramen
.fi
.RE
.PP
Pick 3 winners from a file:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ alea \-\-count 3 \-\-file participants.txt
.fi
.RE
.PP
Schedule a future draw:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ alea \-\-at \(aq2026-07-22T12:00:00+03:00\(aq \-\-count 3 \-\-file participants.txt
.fi
.RE
.PP
Quiet mode for scripting:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ winner=$(alea \-\-quiet \-\-round 6100001 pizza sushi tacos)
.fi
.RE
.PP
Pipe git authors into a draw:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ git log \-\-format="%an" | sort \-u | alea \-\-file \-
.fi
.RE
.SH ALGORITHM
The selection algorithm is intentionally simple so that anyone can verify
a result by hand or with basic shell tools, without needing this program.
.IP 1. 4
Fetch randomness round from https://api.drand.sh/public
.IP 2. 4
Take first 8 hex characters of the randomness field (32 bits)
.IP 3. 4
Compute index = value % option_count
.IP 4. 4
For multiple winners, use next 8-char chunk and remove the winner from the pool
.SH SEE ALSO
.UR https://drand.love
drand
